    "description": "<p>Rutabaga is often seen as a food of last resort, linked to food shortages in wartime. Boiled stew made solely from rutabaga and water is a common dish during major conflicts. Rutabaga roots and tops serve as a valuable forage crop for winter livestock feed.</p>",
    "weight": 0.1,
