    "rarity": "rare",
    "isMagic": true,
    "image": "https://assets.forge-vtt.com/bazaar/core/icons/sundries/scrolls/scroll-bound-sealed-black-red.webp",
    "description": "<p>A spell scroll bears the words of a single spell, written in a mystical cipher. If the spell is on your class's spell list, you can read the scroll and cast its spell without providing any material components. Otherwise, the scroll is unintelligible. Casting the spell by reading the scroll requires the spell's normal casting time. Once the spell is cast, the words on the scroll fade, and it crumbles to dust. If the casting is interrupted, the scroll is not lost.</p><hr /><h3>Creation (Level 5)</h3><hr /><div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>You pull wisps of shadow &amp;Reference[material]{material} from the Shadowfell to create a nonliving object of vegetable matter within range: soft goods, rope, wood, or something similar. You can also use this spell to create mineral objects such as stone, crystal, or metal. The object created must be no larger than a 5-foot &amp;Reference[cube]{cube}, and the object must be of a form and &amp;Reference[material]{material} that you have seen before.</p>\n<p>The duration depends on the object's &amp;Reference[material]{material}. If the object is composed of multiple materials, use the shortest duration.</p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>&amp;Reference[material]{Material}</th>\n<th>Duration</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Vegetable matter</td>\n<td>1 day</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Stone or crystal</td>\n<td>12 hours</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Precious metals</td>\n<td>1 hour</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Gems</td>\n<td>10 minutes</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Adamantine or mithral</td>\n<td>1 minute</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Using any &amp;Reference[material]{material} created by this spell as another spell's &amp;Reference[material]{material} component causes that spell to fail.</p>\n<p><em><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong></em> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 6th level or higher, the &amp;Reference[cube]{cube} increases by 5 feet for each slot level above 5th.</p>\n</div><hr /><h3>Scroll Details</h3><hr />\n<p>If the spell is on your class's spell list but of a higher level than you can normally cast, you must make a DC 15 ability check using your spellcasting ability to determine whether you cast it successfully. On a failed check, the spell disappears from the scroll with no other effect.</p>\n<p>The level of the spell on the scroll determines the spell's saving throw DC and attack bonus, as well as the scroll's rarity.</p>\n<p><strong>Save DC</strong>: 17<br /><strong>Attack Bonus</strong>: +9.</p>\n<p>A wizard spell on a spell scroll can be copied just as spells in spellbooks can be copied. When a spell is copied from a spell scroll, the copier must succeed on a DC 15 Intelligence (Arcana) check. If the check succeeds, the spell is successfully copied. Whether the check succeeds or fails, the spell scroll is destroyed.</p>",
