    "rarity": "uncommon",
    "isMagic": true,
    "image": "https://assets.forge-vtt.com/bazaar/core/icons/sundries/scrolls/scroll-bound-orange-tan.webp",
    "description": "<p>A spell scroll bears the words of a single spell, written in a mystical cipher. If the spell is on your class's spell list, you can read the scroll and cast its spell without providing any material components. Otherwise, the scroll is unintelligible. Casting the spell by reading the scroll requires the spell's normal casting time. Once the spell is cast, the words on the scroll fade, and it crumbles to dust. If the casting is interrupted, the scroll is not lost.</p><hr /><h3>Elemental Weapon (Level 3)</h3><p><em>Requires Concentration</em></p><hr /><div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>A nonmagical weapon you touch becomes a magic weapon. Choose one of the following damage types: &amp;Reference[acid]{acid}, &amp;Reference[cold]{cold}, &amp;Reference[fire]{fire}, &amp;Reference[lightning]{lightning}, or &amp;Reference[thunder]{thunder}. For the duration, the weapon has a +1 bonus to attack rolls and deals an extra 1d4 damage of the chosen type when it hits.</p>\n<p><em><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong></em> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 5th or 6th level, the bonus to attack rolls increases to +2 and the extra damage increases to 2d4. When you use a spell slot of 7th level or higher, the bonus increases to +3 and the extra damage increases to 3d4.</p>\n</div><hr /><h3>Scroll Details</h3><hr />\n<p>If the spell is on your class's spell list but of a higher level than you can normally cast, you must make a DC 13 ability check using your spellcasting ability to determine whether you cast it successfully. On a failed check, the spell disappears from the scroll with no other effect.</p>\n<p>The level of the spell on the scroll determines the spell's saving throw DC and attack bonus, as well as the scroll's rarity.</p>\n<p><strong>Save DC</strong>: 15<br /><strong>Attack Bonus</strong>: +7.</p>\n<p>A wizard spell on a spell scroll can be copied just as spells in spellbooks can be copied. When a spell is copied from a spell scroll, the copier must succeed on a DC 13 Intelligence (Arcana) check. If the check succeeds, the spell is successfully copied. Whether the check succeeds or fails, the spell scroll is destroyed.</p>",
