    "type": "consumable",
    "price": 120,
    "rarity": "uncommon",
    "isMagic": true,
    "image": "https://assets.forge-vtt.com/bazaar/core/icons/sundries/scrolls/scroll-bound-blue-tan.webp",
    "description": "<p>A spell scroll bears the words of a single spell, written in a mystical cipher. If the spell is on your class's spell list, you can read the scroll and cast its spell without providing any material components. Otherwise, the scroll is unintelligible. Casting the spell by reading the scroll requires the spell's normal casting time. Once the spell is cast, the words on the scroll fade, and it crumbles to dust. If the casting is interrupted, the scroll is not lost.</p><hr /><h3>Silence (Level 2)</h3><p><em>Requires Concentration</em></p><hr /><div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>For the duration, no sound can be created within or pass through a 20-foot-radius &amp;Reference[sphere]{sphere} centered on a point you choose within range. Any creature or object entirely inside the &amp;Reference[sphere]{sphere} is immune to &amp;Reference[thunder]{thunder} damage, and creatures are &amp;Reference[deafened]{deafened} while entirely inside it. Casting a spell that includes a &amp;Reference[vocal]{verbal} component is impossible there.</p>\n</div><hr /><h3>Scroll Details</h3><hr />\n<p>If the spell is on your class's spell list but of a higher level than you can normally cast, you must make a DC 12 ability check using your spellcasting ability to determine whether you cast it successfully. On a failed check, the spell disappears from the scroll with no other effect.</p>\n<p>The level of the spell on the scroll determines the spell's saving throw DC and attack bonus, as well as the scroll's rarity.</p>\n<p><strong>Save DC</strong>: 13<br /><strong>Attack Bonus</strong>: +5.</p>\n<p>A wizard spell on a spell scroll can be copied just as spells in spellbooks can be copied. When a spell is copied from a spell scroll, the copier must succeed on a DC 12 Intelligence (Arcana) check. If the check succeeds, the spell is successfully copied. Whether the check succeeds or fails, the spell scroll is destroyed.</p>",
