    "description": "<p>A spell scroll bears the words of a single spell, written in a mystical cipher. If the spell is on your class's spell list, you can read the scroll and cast its spell without providing any material components. Otherwise, the scroll is unintelligible. Casting the spell by reading the scroll requires the spell's normal casting time. Once the spell is cast, the words on the scroll fade, and it crumbles to dust. If the casting is interrupted, the scroll is not lost.</p><hr /><h3>Thunderclap (Level 0)</h3><hr /><div class=\"ddb\">\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">You create a burst of thunderous sound that can be heard up to 100 feet away. Each creature within range, other than you, must succeed on a &amp;Reference[con]{Constitution} saving throw or take 1d6 &amp;Reference[thunder]{thunder} damage.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">The spell’s damage increases by 1d6 when you reach 5th level (2d6), 11th level (3d6), and 17th level (4d6).</p>\n</div><hr /><h3>Scroll Details</h3><hr />\n<p>If the spell is on your class's spell list but of a higher level than you can normally cast, you must make a DC 10 ability check using your spellcasting ability to determine whether you cast it successfully. On a failed check, the spell disappears from the scroll with no other effect.</p>\n<p>The level of the spell on the scroll determines the spell's saving throw DC and attack bonus, as well as the scroll's rarity.</p>\n<p><strong>Save DC</strong>: 13<br /><strong>Attack Bonus</strong>: +5.</p>",
