    "isMagic": false,
    "image": "icons/weapons/polearms/glaive-simple.webp",
    "description": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>A yklwa (pronounced YICK-ul-wah) is a simple melee weapon that is the traditional weapon of Chultan warriors. A yklwa consists of a 3-foot wooden shaft with a steel or stone blade up to 18 inches long. It costs 1 gp, and it deals  [[/damage 1d8 type=piercing average=true]] damage on a hit. Although it has the thrown weapon property, the yklwa is not well balanced for throwing (range 10/30 ft.).</p>\n</div>",
